  "text": "HEV is a spherical, non-enveloped, single-stranded ribonucleic acid (RNA) virus belonging to the Hepeviridae family that contains several viral species divided into two genera: Orthohepevirus with four species (Orthohepevirus A-D) and Piscihepevirus with one species (Piscihepevirus A) [CITATION_1] . Eight genotypes exist within Orthohepevirus A and these HEV strains infect humans and multiple mammals' species. Genotype 1 and 2 are restricted to humans; genotype 3 is found among humans, swine, rabbits, deer and mongooses; genotype 4circulates between humans and swine; genotype 5 and 6 are found in wild boars; and genotype 7 and 8were recently identified in dromedary and Bactrian camels, respectively [CITATION_2] .",
